Usage: set_aocv_interface_path_offset [-help] <derateOffsetVal> [<lib_cells>]
                                      [-cell] [-delay_corner <dc_corner_name>]
                                      [-net]
                                      -power_domain <power_domain_name_list>
                                      [-view <view_name>]

-help                                      # Prints out the command usage
<derateOffsetVal>                          # Value of derate offset
                                           # (float, required)
<lib_cells>                                # Specifies a list of library cells
                                           # for a specific interface derate
                                           # (string, optional)
-cell                                      # Specifies a list of cells
                                           # (bool, optional)
-delay_corner <dc_corner_name>             # Specifies a list of delay corners
                                           # (string, optional)
-net                                       # Applies derate offset to net
                                           # objects only. Default: the derate
                                           # offset value will be applied to
                                           # both the cell and net type of
                                           # objects (bool, optional)
-power_domain <power_domain_name_list>     # Specifies a list of power domains
                                           # (string, required)
-view <view_name>                          # Specifies a list of views
                                           # (string, optional)